  "texts": [
    "Besides a fast algorithm that can compare the input set to all other sets, efficient storage of the gene sets is needed as well as sufficient hardware.",
    "To enable a fast gene set search, a Rustpowered REST API was implemented.",
    "The algorithm first initializes several in-memory data structures: 1) a background sorted set of all genes across all gene sets in the database; 2) the index of each gene saved in a hashmap mapping where each gene is mapped to a 32 bit unsigned integer (U32) index; 3) the gene set IDs and unique hashes stored as UUIDs; and 4) a hashset of mapped genes using the Fowler-Noll-Vo (FNV) hash function on each gene for each unique gene set.",
    "FNV is known to perform well when dealing with small keys.",
    "This is the case in our implementation which uses 32-bit unsigned integer keys."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}